Safe and secure. It does not check for the validity of the JSON string, but shouldn't create any catastrophic errors.</description><name>GooglePlace_JSONParser</name><script><![CDATA[/**
 * Parses JSON string to javascript object
 * 
 * tom.dilatush@service-now.com
 */

var GooglePlace_JSONParser = Class.create();

GooglePlace_JSONParser.prototype = {
    parse: function (source) {
        if (global.JSUtil.nil(source))
            return;

        return new SNC.JSONParse().decode(source);
    }
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2022-03-28 21:14:24</sys_created_on><sys_id>a560a70ddb6a0110487e1c970596198d</sys_id><sys_mod_count>2</sys_mod_count><sys_name>GooglePlace_JSONParser</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Google Location" source="x_481580_google_0">42c79a81db660110487e1c97059619a4</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Google Location">42c79a81db660110487e1c97059619a4</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_a560a70ddb6a0110487e1c970596198d</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-03-28 21:16:23</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>
